              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>The most effective methods are: Google Alerts for your brand name, Ahrefs Content Explorer searching for your brand, Semrush Brand Monitoring, and Mention.com. Search for your exact brand name in quotes on Google and filter to exclude your own domain. Check results page by page for any that reference you without linking.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do unlinked mentions help SEO without being converted to links?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Google has confirmed it understands co-citations — mentions of your brand alongside topic-relevant terms — and uses them as a trust signal even without a link. However, an actual backlink from the same page passes significantly more PageRank. Always prioritise converting unlinked mentions to links before relying on co-citation value alone.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the best way to email a site about an unlinked mention?</span>
